 numbers:
15 commit goals: completed, 7 on track, 2 off track (which one is at highest risk?)
7 stretch goals: 2 deprioritized, 3 on track, 2 off track
8 new goals (added during Q2)

What went well:
Responded well to changing BU priorities - took over and made progress on the Messenger slot - delivered more than planned

What did not go well:
Customer adoption is low and remains low (details below)

Maintenance
Maintenance track for overdeliver for all BUs already delivered 88% of our Q2 orders (80% are on track to overdeliver in Q2 so far).
We removed 62% of our backlog. We have 20 areas on track to eliminate our backlog.
Our backlog will go down when we remove our backlog.

Early Customer Adoption
PMs hired in April were assigned to 3 BUs (Ignite, Jigsaw, Influitive). We made progress on what we would have wanted usage/activity remains low:
Messenger: of 20 customers, 4 customers showed interest, none has concrete plans to switch to our unit until the new version is proven stable or are mid-upgrade with their current unit. Just live wait of 12 customers, 3 are interested in upgrading.

Improvements: we are fixing this by defining the service TPM Slot - Early Adoption Service
Add key takeaways (TPM focus on early adoption, everything else is BU responsibility)
